          <td class="mapping-type-redirect">301</td>
          <td><a href="#redirect">Redirect</a></td>
        </tr>
        <tr id="410">
          <td class="mapping-type-archive">410</td>
          <td><a href="#archive">Archive</a></td>
        </tr>
        <tr id="404">
          <td class="mapping-type-error">404</td>
          <td>Not found, labelled red. If this is returned after switchover it means there is a missing mapping.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3 id="subdomain">Subdomain</h3>
    <p>Subdomains are domain names which have a parent domain name. For example: en.wikipedia.org and www.wikipedia.org are different subdomains of their parent domain wikipedia.org.</p>

    <h3 id="tna">The National Archives (TNA)</h3>
    <p>The National Archives is the government organisation responsible for creating archives of UK government websites to maintain the public record in the digital age. The Transition app provides users with a link to TNA to view archived pages on transitioned sites.</p>
    <p><a href="http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/">Web Archive homepage</a></p>

    <h3 id="tna-timestamp">TNA Timestamp</h3>
    <p>The National Archives Web Archive will produce snapshots (or “crawl”) of a given website, which are labelled with timestamps, for example <code>20100202072553</code> is for a snapshot taken on the 2 February 2010 at 7:25am.</p>

    <h3 id="ttl">Time to live (TTL)</h3>
    <p>The number of seconds for which a <a href="#dns">DNS</a> record can be cached by your computer. For example, before being checked with a DNS server. We ask for the TTL for your sites to be lowered to 5 minutes before switchover so that there is a clean cut-over — rather than different users getting the old or new site until the change has propagated. Commonly TTLs can be set to a day, which would lead to poor user experience as they would see the old or new site unpredictably.</p>

    <h3 id="url">URL</h3>
    <p>A URL is how a web browser requests pages, images and other data from a website.</p>
